OL,3,CExtreme rain leaves farmers with dead
OL,4,Clambs and decimated crops
OL,6,F"It shouldn't stick together like
OL,7,Fthis, it should break apart and
OL,8,Fcrumble between my fingers," Mr
OL,9,FCollins told ITV News.
OL,11,FHe has just three days now to plant
OL,12,F200 acres of wheat to get enough yield
OL,13,Ffor his next harvest, but all he can
OL,14,Fdo is wait until the soil dries out.
OL,16,FSouth west England saw the wettest
OL,17,FFebruary on record earlier this year
OL,18,Fand across the country, there was 29%
OL,19,Fmore rainfall than the average.
