OL,3,CExtreme rain leaves farmers with dead
OL,4,Clambs and decimated crops
OL,6,FReleased back into the fields between
OL,7,F24 and 48-hours-old, the churned wet
OL,8,Fsoil is too thick for the newborn
OL,9,Flambs to walk in, causing them to
OL,10,Fbecome stuck and die.
OL,12,FMathew Issac, a sheep farmer in Wales,
OL,13,Fsays he's lost 30 livestock so far.
OL,15,F"Anything that's a little bit weak
OL,16,Fthey fall by the wayside," he told ITV
OL,17,FNews.
OL,19,F"You're picking up dead lambs in the
OL,20,Fmorning then, so it's not good."
