OL,4,Clambs and decimated crops
OL,6,FMany whose fields are still submerged
OL,7,Fsay they're struggling to keep their
OL,8,Fbusinesses afloat, and the Agriculture
OL,9,Fand Horticulture Development Board
OL,10,F(AHDB) say a rise in food prices is
OL,11,Fnow inevitable.
OL,13,FJack Watts, Head of Economics Strategy
OL,14,Fat the AHDB, said: "If we don't make
OL,15,Fenough wheat here, we have to rely
OL,16,Fmore on imports and that increases
OL,17,Fcosts for manufacturers."
